<paragraph id="25262F0E1031FFAEDBB2FAC84D4E2EB0" blockId="20.[151,504,1374,1437]" box="[151,379,1411,1437]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
(
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDBBAFAC84D142EB0" box="[159,289,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[158,1424,181,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[158,1430,181,1782]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Asianthrips species. A. magnus, 11–12; (11) Female (mac); (12) Female (mic). A. malayanus, 13–14; (13), Female (mac); (14) Non-paratypic female (mic). A. nobilis, 15–16; (15) Female (mac); (16) Female (mic). A. orientalis, 17–18; (17) Female (mac); (18) Male (mic). A. pallens, 19–20; (19) Female (mac); (20) Male (mic). A. parvinotus, 21–22; (21) Female (mac); (22) Male, non-paratype (mic)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404870" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404870/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Figs 13–14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDA09FAC84D462EB0" box="[300,371,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–93" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-76@21.[229,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 88–93. Asianthrips malayanus, sp. n., female. (88) Head–pelta (mac); (89) Head–pelta (mic); (90) Antenna (mac); (91) Mesopresternum (mac); (92) Tergites II–III(mac); (93) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404904/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">88–93</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1031FFAFDBB2FA804FD82BD4" blockId="20.[151,1437,1483,2013]" lastBlockId="21.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1031FFAEDBB2FA804D402EC9" box="[151,373,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Body brown (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAED93BFA804E472EC8" box="[542,626,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[158,1424,181,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[158,1430,181,1782]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Asianthrips species. A. magnus, 11–12; (11) Female (mac); (12) Female (mic). A. malayanus, 13–14; (13), Female (mac); (14) Non-paratypic female (mic). A. nobilis, 15–16; (15) Female (mac); (16) Female (mic). A. orientalis, 17–18; (17) Female (mac); (18) Male (mic). A. pallens, 19–20; (19) Female (mac); (20) Male (mic). A. parvinotus, 21–22; (21) Female (mac); (22) Male, non-paratype (mic)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404870" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404870/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Antennal segment III yellow, weakly shaded with brown at apical 1/2, segment IV somewhat yellowish at basal 1/3, the remainings of antennae brown. All femora brown, concolourous with body; tibiae yellow, weakly shaded with brown medially; all tarsi yellow. Fore wings very weakly shaded with brown; body setae pale. Head (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDAD8F97C4E642D7C" box="[509,593,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–93" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-76@21.[229,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 88–93. Asianthrips malayanus, sp. n., female. (88) Head–pelta (mac); (89) Head–pelta (mic); (90) Antenna (mac); (91) Mesopresternum (mac); (92) Tergites II–III(mac); (93) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404904/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
) almost as long as wide, but a little longer than wide in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1031FFAEDFC5F97C49752D7C" box="[1248,1344,1591,1617]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">paratype</typeStatus>
female, 1.08 times as long as wide (see Remarks); dorsal surface sculptured with transverse reticulation, the reticles very weak between eyes, with longitudinal weak reticulation or striae between posterior ocelli. Cheeks very weakly rounded, weakly narrowed to base. Postocular setae longer than eye. Postocellar setae almost as long as a diameter of posterior ocellus or shorter. Eyes 0.41–0.42 times as long as head in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1031FFAED8CEF98C48642DCC" box="[1003,1105,1735,1761]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">holotype</typeStatus>
. Antennal segments VII and VIII somewhat broadly fused, segment VIII not constricted basally, cone-shaped (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDF12F9A048B92C28" box="[1079,1164,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–93" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-76@21.[229,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 88–93. Asianthrips malayanus, sp. n., female. (88) Head–pelta (mac); (89) Head–pelta (mic); (90) Antenna (mac); (91) Mesopresternum (mac); (92) Tergites II–III(mac); (93) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404904/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 90</figureCitation>
); segment III with three sense cones. Maxillary stylets short and V-shaped, similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1031FFAED881F84448AC2C04" box="[932,1177,1807,1833]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1031FFAED881F844480B2C04" box="[932,1086,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Bamboosiella</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, retracted only to basal collar of head. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDAE3F8784E2C2C60" box="[454,537,1843,1869]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–93" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-76@21.[229,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 88–93. Asianthrips malayanus, sp. n., female. (88) Head–pelta (mac); (89) Head–pelta (mic); (90) Antenna (mac); (91) Mesopresternum (mac); (92) Tergites II–III(mac); (93) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404904/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
) 0.73 times as long as head and 1.92 times as wide as long in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1031FFAEDFD4F87849622C60" box="[1265,1367,1843,1869]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">holotype</typeStatus>
; epim the longest; pa about 1/2 of the median pronotal length. Metanotum polygonally reticulated anteriorly, but weak, longitudinally reticulated posteriorly. Prospinasternum well developed. Mesopresternum and mesoeusternum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDE4AF8304C812C94" captionStart="FIGURES 88–93" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-76@21.[229,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 88–93. Asianthrips malayanus, sp. n., female. (88) Head–pelta (mac); (89) Head–pelta (mic); (90) Antenna (mac); (91) Mesopresternum (mac); (92) Tergites II–III(mac); (93) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404904/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
) comparatively widely fused medially, with distinct sutures between them at both sides. Fore tarsi unarmed. Fore wings with 5–5 duplicated cilia. Tergites comparatively small (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAED84BF8884FF12CF0" box="[878,964,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–93" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-76@21.[229,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 88–93. Asianthrips malayanus, sp. n., female. (88) Head–pelta (mac); (89) Head–pelta (mic); (90) Antenna (mac); (91) Mesopresternum (mac); (92) Tergites II–III(mac); (93) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404904/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 92</figureCitation>
), but tergites III–V wider than pronotum (tergite V of 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1030FFAFDA0CFFDC4DBE2B9C" box="[297,395,151,177]" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">holotype</typeStatus>
almost as wide as pronotum, but this may be due to cover slip pressure). S1 setae on tergite IX a little longer than S2, 0.76–0.79 times as long as tube, S1 weakly expanded, S2 very weakly expanded at apex. Tube (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1030FFAFDBFAFF944D052BD4" box="[223,304,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–93" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-76@21.[229,1359,273,1864]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 88–93. Asianthrips malayanus, sp. n., female. (88) Head–pelta (mac); (89) Head–pelta (mic); (90) Antenna (mac); (91) Mesopresternum (mac); (92) Tergites II–III(mac); (93) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404904/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
) 0.71 times as long as head. Anal setae almost as long as tube.
</paragraph>
<caption id="71E67F861030FFAFDBB2F8144F462CB1" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404904" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6404904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404904/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" startId="21.[151,264,1887,1911]" targetBox="[230,1359,273,1864]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph id="25262F0E1030FFAFDBB2F8144F462CB1" blockId="21.[151,1436,1887,1948]" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1030FFAFDBB2F8144D602C5A" bold="true" box="[151,341,1887,1911]" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">FIGURES 88–93.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1030FFAFDA7EF8144E702C5A" authority="Okajima &amp; Masumoto, 2022" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[347,581,1887,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malayanus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1030FFAFDA7EF8144E702C5A" box="[347,581,1887,1911]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">Asianthrips malayanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1030FFAFD977F82B4EBE2C55" bold="true" box="[594,651,1888,1912]" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0CDE4E671030FFAFD977F82B4EBE2C55" box="[594,651,1888,1912]" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female. (88) Head–pelta (mac); (89) Head–pelta (mic); (90) Antenna (mac); (91) Mesopresternum (mac); (92) Tergites II–III(mac); (93) Tube (mac).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1033FFACDBE2FFDC491E2A6C" blockId="22.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1033FFACDBE2FFDC4D432B9C" bold="true" box="[199,374,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">Measurements</emphasis>
. Female 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1033FFACDAC0FFDC4E722B9C" box="[485,583,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">holotype</typeStatus>
(mac.) in microns. Distended body length about 2000. Head length 171, width across cheeks 170. Compound eye dorsal length 70–71. Pronotum length 125, width 240. Fore wing length about 860. Tube length 121, width across base 60. Antenna length 395, segments III–VIII length (width) as follows: 58 (30), 65 (30), 53 (27), 50 (25), 46 (22), 31 (15). Postocular setae 73–79. Pronotal aa 42–45, am 43–44, ml 57–62, pa 63–63, epim 70–70. S1 setae on tergite IX 92–96, S2 setae on tergite IX 85–92. Anal setae about 120.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1033FFACDBE2FE004E752AA4" blockId="22.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1033FFACDBE2FE004DA12A49" box="[199,404,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">Male macroptera.</emphasis>
Very similar in colour and structure to macropterous female, but body smaller. Fore tarsi unarmed. Anal setae longer than tube.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1033FFACDBE2FED84FF92910" blockId="22.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1033FFACDBE2FED84D432A80" bold="true" box="[199,374,403,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">Measurements</emphasis>
. Male 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1033FFACDAE0FED84E102A80" box="[453,549,403,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="123">paratype</typeStatus>
(mac.) in microns. Distended body length 1550. Head length 155, width across cheeks 142. Compound eye dorsal length 65. Pronotum length 100, width 171. Fore wing length about 710. Tube length?80, width across base 50. Antenna length 355, segments III–VIII length (width) as follows: 53 (27), 55 (28), 47 (25), 48 (22), 42 (20), 30 (14). Postocular setae?55. Pronotal aa?, am?, ml?, pa about 50, epim?55. S1 setae on tergite IX about 80, S2 setae on tergite IX 33–36. Anal setae 100–110.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
